body:
Compiling the following module (called `my_test.sv`) with `verilator --binary --trace --assert -Wno-PINCONNECTEMPTY my_test.sv` and running it with `./obj_dir/Vmy_test` yields at the end `Should not get here, the task blocks indefinately` while it should be `Task exited`. The reason for it is that the passing by reference to the task does not work and it is just passed by value.

The received output is
```
Starting task
0
1
Should not get here, the task blocks indefinately
```

while it should be

```
Starting task
0
1
2
Task exited
```

```
`default_nettype none

module my_test();
    var logic   rst_bi;
    var logic   clk_i;

    initial begin
        wait (rst_bi == 1'b1);
        while (rst_bi == 1'b1) begin
            clk_i = ~clk_i;
            #10;
        end
    end

    task automatic test_task(ref logic clk);
        $display("0");
        wait (clk == 1'b0);
        $display("1");
        wait (clk == 1'b1);
        $display("2");
    endtask

    initial begin
        $dumpfile("test.vcd");
        $dumpvars;
        rst_bi = 1'b0;
        clk_i = 1'b0;
        #10;
        rst_bi = 1'b1;
        #10;
        wait (clk_i == 1'b0);
        $display("Starting task");
        test_task(clk_i);
        $display("Task exited");
        #100;
        $finish;
    end

    initial begin
        #1000;
        $display("Should not get here, the task blocks indefinately");
        $finish;
    end
endmodule

`default_nettype wire

```
